dct_description_sm: Alternate title: Kagi. In upper left margin: Fomosa city plans 1:10,000. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. Compiled from aerial photography dated January 1999, by photo-planimetric method and by reference to Formosa 1:50,000, A.M.S. Sheet 2117-II, 1944; Japanese Imperial Land Survey, Kagi, 1928; Town Plan of Kagi 1:11,000 (approx)., OSS, 1944; Town Plan of Kagi (Japanese Source), 1935. Additional information from intelligence data. Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. Military grid. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. "Contour interval 10 meters, with auxiliary contours at 5 meter intervals." Three classes of roads or trails, four classes of railroads, two types of internal boundaries, and areas of vegetation and cultivation are shown. Some buildings and regional districts are named. "Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) system." Includes "Glossary." Marginal maps and diagrams: Index to boundaries -- Coverage diagram. South Decimal Degree 23.450000. AMS 1. West Decimal Degree 120.383333. East Decimal Degree 120.450000. North Decimal Degree 23.483333.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
